{
  "texts": [
    "These technologies can either enhance engagement with the profession or, if not carefully implemented, lead to disengagement and harm human-animal relationships.",
    "Studies suggest that relational practices could facilitate the use of new technologies throughout the animal's life cycle (139, 140).",
    "Similar concerns have been expressed by researchers examining technologies designed for companion animals.",
    "For example, remote human-dog interaction applications that allow humans to feed or talk to their dogs while they are alone at home could encourage owners to leave their dogs at home for even longer periods, exacerbating the very issue the technologies were designed to alleviate (141, 142).",
    "Another example involves health monitoring devices for companion cats, which may lead owners to misinterpret their animals' health conditions and even disregard veterinary advice (143, 144)."
  ]
}